premise_source_doc_sentence: Amitriptyline , sold under the brand name Elavil among others , is a medicine used to treat a number of mental illnesses .

However , in clinical trials , using similar doses , butriptyline was found to be even more effective than amitriptyline as an antidepressant , despite the fact that amitriptyline is far stronger as both a 5-HT2 antagonist and serotonin-norepinephrine reuptake inhibitor .

Amitriptyline/perphenazine  (  Duo-Vil , Etrafon , Triavil , Triptafen  )  is a formulation that contains the tricyclic antidepressant amitriptyline and the medium-potency typical  (  first-generation  )  antipsychotic , perphenazine .

Amitriptylinoxide  (  Amioxid , Ambivalon , Equilibrin  )  , or amitriptyline N-oxide , is a tricyclic antidepressant  (  TCA  )  which was introduced in Europe in the 1970s for the treatment of depression .
It is the isobutyl side chain homologue of amitriptyline and produces similar effects to it , but with less marked side effects like sedation and interactions with adrenergic drugs .
